Photo by Investopedia on August 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Understanding Stagflation Stagflation was long believed to be impossible because widely accepted economic theories from the 19th century ruled out such a model. The Great Depression and emergence of Keynesian economics caused economists to reevaluate inflation and unemployment. Stagflation is an example of how economic data can sometimes conflict with popular theories and policies. Investopedia'.

Photo by Investopedia on August 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Causes of Stagflation Oil Prices A sudden increase in oil prices reduces a country's economic output. Photo by Investopedia on July 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Understanding Earnings Earnings measure the amount of profit generated within specific period of time. They represent a direct link to a company's financial performance. Both analysts and investors have expectations for a company's earnings. Earnings that are different from estimates can impact the stock price. A company that "beats," or exceeds, expectations is looked more favorably for investors. company "misses" earnings, t's often considered an unattractive investment. Investopedia'.

Photo by Investopedia on July 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Measures of Earnings Earnings Before Taxes (EBT) company's pre-tax income. Earnings Before Interest and Taxes (EBIT) Calculated as revenue minus expenses excluding tax and interest. Earnings Before Interest, Taxes, Depreciation, and Amortization (EBITDA) Similar to free cash flow. It excludes interest and non-cash expenses. Investopedia'.

Photo by Investopedia on July 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Criticism of Earnings There is continuous pressure from investors and analysts for a company to consistently beat earnings expectations. A criticism of earnings is that a company may forgo long-term decisions that are in the company's interest because the cost associated with them will decrease current earnings. Managers also may be tempted to manipulate earnings because earnings are such a crucial metric. This is illegal and unethical. Investopedia'.
